What cookies do?

Cookies refer to small data files that are downloaded onto your device when you visit a website. When you revisit the same website, these cookies ensure that your device is recognized. Through the use of cookies and similar technologies like pixel tags/beacons and scripts, websites can store information about visits and their visitors. This information may include your IP address, the type of device you use, and your browsing behavior, such as specific web pages visited and website navigation.

We employ two types of cookies: session cookies, which are deleted when you close your browser, and persistent cookies, which remain on your device for a predetermined period. Some cookies are placed by us, while others are placed by third parties. Third-party cookies may collect data beyond our own website.
What categories of cookies are utilized on this website?

This website exclusively employs functional and analytical cookies, which are essential for the proper functioning of the website. These cookies do not necessitate your explicit consent and are automatically placed on your browser when you use this website.
Functional Cookies

Functional cookies are essential for ensuring proper functionality and usability of our website. These cookies enable you to view and navigate our website seamlessly. They are also utilized to remember your language preferences and cookie settings. Additionally, functional cookies facilitate A/B testing, allowing us to experiment with new features, various versions, and designs of our website. It's important to note that the information gathered through these cookies is not used for marketing purposes. These cookies are vital for the optimal use of our website. If you choose to block this type of cookie in your browser, it may adversely affect the functionality of our website, and certain features may become unavailable.
Analytical Cookies

Analytical cookies collect aggregated information about how visitors utilize our website. This includes data on the most frequently visited pages, duration of visits, and any encountered errors. Furthermore, these cookies are employed for conducting user surveys and gathering feedback from visitors regarding our website as a whole or specific elements of it. The information derived from these cookies aids us in comprehending which sections of our website attract the most interest from our visitors and enables us to enhance the overall quality of our website.

"Give us the time frame by which you need your shipment to arrive and leave the worries to us."

Is the linestopper hanging in the air at the car factory? Do you have an excellent business opportunity where timing to market is the key? Then there is a priority air/ground cargo service for you, especially suitable if you are very concerned about the delivery time. We see a story in every shipment, even on a non-financial level. We believe that the shipping business is about personal relationships and failure to meet deadlines can have unfathomable financial and non-financial consequences.

This service bypasses the economic service bottlenecks of dual airport warehouse handling and the airline-organized truck, which often awaits until enough shipments have accumulated to make the airport pick-up organization profitable.
Guarantee! If, for any reason within WE-DEL's control, the transit time is not met, you will be invoiced for the price of the Budget service instead of the price of the Smart service.
Give us your budget for transportation, we will try to find a solution through ground or air partial loading.

Budget is an economic service where the lowest possible price is a priority, in the case of air transport, the transit time is within 14 days from dispatch. In the case of land transport, we will try to find capacity nearby, thereby saving costs and the environment in order to maximize the utilization of the given means of transport.
We will be very happy if you turn to us with confidence with your request for transport services.

Tailored Solution for Your Freight Success

We don't want a world full of corporations where we become just passive recipients of the decision which international corporation to choose despite all of them has the same services wrapped in a different marketing package. Big corporations are usually doing services for another big corporations and small and medium enterprises are not getting service with the same quality and price. With this vision, we decided to found WE-DEL. Small and medium-sized enterprises are the healthy backbone of our economy, yet their share of GDP in the Czech Republic is below the level of the EU28. To a certain extent, this is also due to the fact that the mentioned enterprises encounter barriers from the large players from various sectors in the market. We want to change that!
Our vision is to help especially small and medium-sized companies by offering comprehensive transport services that will help our business partners save costs, time and nerves.

What is your prefered mean of communication?

At first there are three means of communication – online chat, email and call. For order/quote related communication e-mail is essential, while phone call is the fastest mean of communication. In case you dislike anything, do not hesitate to give us a call so we can find a address your feedback. As foretold – feedback is mother of partnership and mutually beneficient cooperation.
Can I ship all around the world with WE-DEL?

Well, almost yes! Of course there are some exceptions. We can’t offer shipment to: Cuba, North Korea, Iran, Syria, Belarus, Sudan, South Sudan, Yemen, Somalia, Burma (Maymar) and of course to Russia. At WE-DEL we believe that the firm spine is more important then profit. Additional check-ups may apply to the shipment that raise a suspicion that might be transfered to Russia through various transit countries.
Which shipments is WE-DEL able to transfer?

WE-DEL is able to transfer everything via Air/ground transport. Our service is mostly designed for time-critical shipments and cost-effective shipments above 70 kg. But no worries – we can also provide you transport or smaller parcels via our courier partners for competitive prices.
Are you working during holidays/weekends?

At WE-DEL ve value your time a lot. Therefore you can approach as anytime via phone call. At our regular work hours, which is from Monday to Friday 08-17 CET we will try our utmost best tol reply you within one hour from sending of mail infromation. For OnTime service you can give us a call 24/7/365.
Is my shipment insured against any damage/losage of cargo?

As a freight forwarding company the cargo you are shipping with us is governed by insurance of our carrier. With that said it is by Montreal & Warszaw agreement in the case of air transport and by CMR in case of ground transport. On top of it WE-DEL has insurance with limit 3 000 000 CZK for freight-forwarding related mistakes. If your shipment exceeds this amouth, do not hesitate to write us for additional insurance.
How can I track my shipment?

We are having tracking option on the page. If for any reason the tracking is not giving updated informations we are always awailable to check the shipment progress via phone/mail/online chat. As for our premium service OnTime we are offering 24/7 tracking.

General forwarding Terms and Conditions

These General Forwarding Terms and Conditions (hereinafter referred to as "GFC") of the companyWE-DEL s.r.o., ID No.: 192 03 462, with registered office at Aviatická 1092/8, Ruzyně, 161 00Praha 6, registered in the Commercial Register kept at the Municipal Court in Prague under the registration number C 383004 (hereinafter referred to as "Forwarder"), regulate in accordance with the provisions of § 1751(1) of Act No. 89/2012 Coll, Civil Code, as amended (hereinafter referred to as the "CC") in conjunction with the provisions of § 2471 et seq. of the CC, the mutual rights and obligations of the Freight Forwarder (as the Freight Forwarder) and its customers (as the Principal) (hereinafter referred to as the "Principal") arising in connection with or on the basis of freight forwarding contracts (hereinafter referred to as the "Freight Forwarding Contract" or the "FFC") concluded in the course of the Freight Forwarder's business between the Freight Forwarder and the Principal.

These T&C apply to cases where the person of the Principal who intends to conclude a Forwarding Contract with the Forwarder is a legal person or a person who acts in the course of concluding the T&C in the course of his/her business activity or in the course of his/her independent exercise of his/her profession.

1. Introductory provisions

1.1 By the Forwarding Agreement, the Forwarder undertakes to arrange for the transport (hereinafter referred to as "Transport") of the agreed consignment (i.e. the item that has been handed over by the Principal for the provision of the forwarding service under the GTC) (hereinafter referred to as "Shipment") from the place specified in the GTC (hereinafter referred to as "Place of Handover") to another place specified in the GTC (hereinafter referred to as "Destination"), by a non-transportation company selected by the Sender under the PO (who shall, for the account of the Principal, transport the Shipment from the Place of Delivery to the Destination on the terms and conditions set out in the PO) (hereinafter referred to as "Carrier"), or procure or perform the acts related to such carriage and agreed in the PO, and the Principal agrees to pay the Sender a fee (hereinafter referred to as "Fee") in respect thereof.

1.2 These T&C form an integral part of any Forwarding Contract, whether made orally or by email, in writing or by implication, pursuant to which the Forwarder undertakes to arrange for the carriage of the Shipment and the Principal undertakes to pay the Forwarder the Fee. These T&Cs thus bind the relationship arising between the Sender and the Principal in arranging the Carriage of Shipments.

1.3 Arrangements deviating from the GTC may be negotiated in the Forwarding Agreement. In accordance with Section 1751(1) of the CC, the provisions of the GTC shall prevail over the provisions of the GTC.

1.4 The Sender may change or supplement the wording of these GTC. However, this provision shall not affect the rights and obligations arising during the period of validity of the previous version of the GTC.
2. Conclusion of the Forwarding Agreement
I. specification of the Principal;

2.1 The Forwarding Contract between the Forwarder and the Principal will normally be concluded electronically on the basis of an Order Form (hereinafter referred to as the "Form"), a general specimen of which may be provided by the Forwarder to the Principal prior to the conclusion of the Contract, and which the Principal will return (usually by e-mail) to the Forwarder after it has been duly completed (see below). The form completed by the Principal will generally contain the following sub-essentials of the ToR:
II. the specification of the Shipment (in particular the weight, size and shape of the Shipment and the nature of its contents);
III. the place and time of Delivery of the Shipment to the Sender and/or directly to the Carrier by the Principal;
IV. The destination and specification of the recipient of the Shipment;
V. contact information of the Principal and the recipient of the Shipment;

2.2 If the Form is absent in a particular case, it and the legal and other consequences provided for in this GTC shall be replaced by an e-mail or other form of communication between the Principal and the Sender (hereinafter referred to as "Communication") containing, in particular, the above described sub-essential elements of the GTC. The Principal shall be fully responsible for the accuracy of all information contained in the Form and/or the Communication, as well as for the accuracy of all information contained in other e-mail and other communications with the Sender. Also, by completing the Form and sending it to the Sender and/or by the Principal's continuation of the Communication even after the Principal has been presented with these T&Cs by the Sender (even if only electronically), the Principal agrees to these T&Cs as an integral part of the Principal's requested Shipper Agreement.

2.3 If the Sender finds that the Form received by it and completed by the Principal is incomplete and/or vague and/or the information received by it from the Principal in the Communication is incomplete and/or vague, it is entitled to invite the Principal to complete or clarify the Form and/or the Communication. The Sender reserves the right to reject and/or not respond to any Form and/or Communication received by the Sender.

2.4 Following the Form completed by the Principal and received by the Freight Forwarder and/or the Communication between the Principal and the Freight Forwarder, the Freight Forwarder shall process the Form and/or the Communication, if applicable, remove its defects and/or deficiencies and/or inadequacies, and deliver to the Principal (usually by e-mail) a draft of, as a rule, the following additional material elements of the Freight Forwarding Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the "Offer"):
I. the place and time of Delivery of the Shipment to the Sender and/or directly to the Carrier by the Principal;
II. approximate transit time (i.e. the time likely to be required to deliver the Shipment from the Place of Receipt to the Destination);
III. The Remuneration and any other costs of the Carriage (including any VAT);
IV. identification of the Carrier who will perform the Carriage;
V. the validity of the Offer.
2.5 The Offer remains valid at all times for the period specified in the Offer.

2.6 The forwarding contract is subsequently concluded at the moment of confirmation of the Offer by the Principal (usually by e-mail). The concluded Forwarding Contract shall be deemed to be executed by the Forwarder at the moment when the Forwarder concludes the relevant contract for the carriage of the Shipment with the Carrier agreed in the ToR. The Sender shall be responsible for the transportation of the Shipment to the Destination only in the cases and in the manner set out below in these GTC.

2.7 The terms and conditions of carriage of the Shipment shall be governed by the terms and conditions of carriage of the relevant Carrier. These conditions will be provided by the Sender to the Principal on request.
2.8 In the event that:
a. The Sender discovers that the information provided by the Principal (primarily, but not exclusively, in the Form and/or Communication) is incorrect and/or incomplete; and/or
b. The Sender has breached any of its obligations set out in these T&Cs and/or obligations under generally applicable law; and/or
c. The Shipment for any reason violates and/or threatens to violate generally binding legal provisions and/or causes the Sender and/or third persons; and/or
d. The Shipment cannot be delivered to the Destination and/or to the recipient designated by the Principal
The shipment cannot be reached;

the Sender is entitled to terminate the Covenant without notice. Termination of the PO by the Sender shall not affect the Sender's right to payment of the Price (see below). In the event of a wrongful termination of the GTC by the Freight Forwarder, the Freight Forwarder shall furthermore be entitled to compensation for damages against the Principal.
3. Rights and obligations of the Principal
3.1 The Principal is obliged in particular, but not exclusively, to:

a. to provide the Sender with complete and correct information about the content and nature of the Shipment, as well as about other facts necessary and decisive for the purpose of concluding the Shipper's Agreement and the contract of carriage, even before the conclusion of the Contract of Carriage (in particular, but not exclusively, about the weight, type, number of pieces, dimensions, method of packing, non/security of the Shipment, etc.), with the understanding that any consequences of incorrect and incomplete information shall always be borne by the Sender;

b. to warn the Sender, prior to the conclusion of the Contract, of the public law and/or customs obligations associated with the Shipment and that the Principal shall be liable to the Sender for all consequences of such omission;
c. In particular, to pack the Shipment properly in accordance with these GTC and general customs and regulations;
d. ensure the characteristics of the Shipment as agreed upon by the Sender in particular in these GTC;

e. in the event that the Shipment is in imminent danger of damage and/or other circumstances threatening or preventing the Shipment have occurred, upon the Sender's request immediately provide the Sender with any further instructions and/or data and/or documents requested by the Sender;
f. pay the agreed Remuneration to the Sender in due and timely manner;
g. inform the Sender without undue delay of any fact affecting the Carriage and/or the proper performance of the Sender's obligations under the GTS;

3.2 In particular, the Principal is not entitled to use the Shipment for a purpose that is contrary to the administrative regulations in force in the EU, the USA and/or the Czech Republic, and/or contrary to the laws of the country of destination, and/or contrary to the laws of the countries through which the Shipment will be transported.
4. Packaging and contents of the Shipment as agreed by the Freight forwarder
A. Packing of the Shipment
4.1 The Principal undertakes, depending on the nature of the contents of the Shipment, to pack the Shipment properly before delivery to the Delivery Point, in particular so that:
a. The Consignment shall always consist of the number of packages / loads agreed in advance between the Sender and the Principal;
b. the packaging complies with general practices and generally applicable laws and regulations;
c. the contents of the Shipment were secured against movement;

d. the packaging of the Shipment provided adequate protection for the contents of the Shipment (including natural protection from adverse weather conditions and influences, and including natural protection during normal and/or Principal-imposed handling of the Shipment);
e. the packaging of the Shipment allows for safe handling of the Shipment;
f. the Shipment did not endanger other shipments being transported together, the means of transport used, the Sender's or Carrier's storage facilities or the means of mechanised handling;

g. The shipment did not endanger the life, health and safety of persons who come into contact with the shipment, allowing for the transport of shipments in layers on the loading area of the transport means, observing elementary caution and professional care;
h. the packaging of the Shipment is integral, regular in shape (except in cases agreed in advance with the Principal where an increased level of risk arising from partial loss is agreed);

i. the Shipment has been properly marked (at least with the identification data of the Principal; the identification data of the Destination and the Recipient; as well as other data that are desirable to facilitate the handling of the Shipment and/or to eliminate the risk of confusion and/or to prevent damage;);
B. Contents of the Shipment

4.2 The Sender understands and the Principal undertakes that the contents of the Shipment shall not (unless otherwise expressly agreed between the Sender and the Principal in the Forwarding Agreement):

a. objects and substances endangering human life or health, such as explosives, weapons, ammunition, rockets, bombs, grenades, combat vehicles, narcotic and psychotropic substances, flammable substances with low flash point, chemical substances and/or chemical preparations, poisons, radioactive substances, corrosives, gases and liquids in pressurized containers, etc;

b. Objects and substances of exceptionally high value such as gold, silver, precious stones, precious metals, art objects, collections, banknotes, coins, activated payment and other monetary cards and valuables except for food stamps, mobile phone charging coupons, SIM cards, vignettes, winning lottery tickets and telephone cards of fixed telephone operators, the maximum value of which in one Shipment does not exceed CZK 10,000 (the Principal is obliged to notify the Sender in advance of any value higher than this);
c. objects and substances that are easily damaged even if the instructions for special handling of the Shipment are followed, such as alcohol and other precious liquids in glass bottles, etc;
d. items and substances subject to temperature changes, such as perishable goods, medical material (blood samples and derivatives), live plants, etc.;
e. live animals and organisms, plants, human and animal remains, etc;
f. meat and meat products, spirits, tobacco products;
g. other articles and substances which, by their nature, require special vehicle arrangements or special conditions for carriage under the applicable regulations (such as bulk substrates, etc.);

4.3 The Principal shall inform third parties who may be forwarding the Shipment for Carriage of the above mentioned packaging and content characteristics and shall ensure that all Shipments forwarded for Carriage under the Shipper Agreement comply with the above mentioned packaging and content characteristics. The Principal shall be liable for failure to comply with this obligation in the same manner as if the Principal had handed over the Shipment for Carriage.

4.4 Consignments with a total value exceeding CZK 500,000 may be transported only by individual written agreement between the Sender and the Principal, whereby the Principal must specify the type of goods to be transported and their actual value/price in the Form and/or in the Communication when transporting such Consignments. For the carriage of Shipments whose value/price is higher than 500.000, - CZK, the Sender strongly recommends that the Principal himself or through the Sender, insures the Shipment for its full actual price.
5. Rights and Obligations of the Freight forwarder
5.1 Freight forwarder:
a. arrange the Carriage with professional care and in negotiating the method and terms of Carriage in the best interests of the Principal under the Shipper's Contract;

b. arrange for insurance of the Shipment only if expressly agreed with the Principal in the Forwarding Agreement (the Forwarder is not entitled and/or obliged to treat a mere indication of the price/value of the Shipment as an instruction from the Principal to insure the Shipment). If insurance of the Shipment is expressly agreed in the PO, the Sender shall insure the Shipment according to the insurance conditions customary in the place of performance. If an insured event occurs, the Freight Forwarder shall fulfil its obligations to the Principal by assigning its claims against the insurance company to the Principal;
c. is not obliged to review and/or supplement the information provided by the Principal, unless this is expressly agreed in the ToR;

d. is entitled to exercise its lien and/or retention over the Shipment for the purpose of securing all its claims and demands against the Principal arising out of and/or in connection with the Form and/or the Communication and/or the PO;

e. act in its sole discretion in preserving the interests of the Principal, in particular in the choice of means of transport and route, if it has not received sufficient and/or practicable instructions from the Principal;

f. be entitled to carry out the Carriage of the Shipment itself, provided that such carriage does not contravene the provisions of the GTC (if the Sender carries out the Carriage of the Shipment itself, it is responsible for the proper carriage of the Shipment in its capacity as Carrier).
6. Remuneration and transport costs

6.1 The Principal agrees to pay the Freight Forwarder the Fee agreed in the Forwarding Agreement and all costs incurred by the Freight Forwarder in arranging the Carriage of the Shipment such as freight, duties, taxes, insurance and other charges (hereinafter referred to as "Carriage Charges").

6.2 The Remuneration and the Carriage Charges shall always be paid by the Principal to the Forwarder jointly in the form of the Forwarder's price (the "Price") without distinction as to the specific proportion of the Remuneration and the Carriage Charges unless otherwise agreed in a particular case. The amount of the Price will be agreed in each individual case of the Shipment in the Forwarding Agreement.

6.3 Unless otherwise agreed in a particular case, the Price is always expressed exclusive of VAT.Therefore, VAT at the statutory rate will always be added to the Price agreed in the PO if the relevant performance is subject to such tax.
6.4 The Price shall be unilaterally increased by the Sender in the event of unforeseen delays in the transport of the Shipment (e.g. unsuccessful arrival, return journey, etc.).

6.5 The Sender's right against the Principal to payment of the Price shall arise for the Sender at the time of conclusion of the Forwarding Agreement. The Freight Forwarder shall always invoice the Principal for the Price before the Shipment is transported by means of a proper tax document (usually sent to the Principal by e-mail) with a maximum due date of 30 days.The Freight Forwarder reserves the right to commence performance under the GTC only after prior payment of the Price by the Customer to the Freight Forwarder in accordance with the issued tax document. If the Principal fails to make proper and timely payment of the Price in accordance with the issued tax invoice, the Principal shall have the right to withdraw from the PO in its entirety.

6.6 In the event of delay by the Principal in payment of the Price, the Sender shall be entitled to a contractual penalty of 0.5% of the amount due for each (even commenced) day of delay. Any right of the Sender to payment of the contractual penalty pursuant to the preceding sentence shall not affect any right of the Sender to compensation for damages incurred by the Sender as a result of the breach of the Principal's obligation to which the contractual penalty relates.Any withdrawal of the Sender from the GTC shall not affect the right of the Sender to payment of the contractual penalty pursuant to the first sentence of this paragraph.

6.7 The Principal acknowledges that the Price is always calculated by the Sender on the basis of the information and data provided by the Principal in the Form and/or in the Communication and related e-mail or other communication with the Sender. In the event that the information and/or data provided by the Principal in the Form and/or in the Communication is found to be inaccurate, incomplete or false (e.g. the weight, dimensions, shape or type and content of the Shipment, etc. ) and/or in the event that the Sender breaches any of its obligations set out in these GTC and/or any other legally binding regulations and/or in the event that the Sender and/or the Carrier incurs additional costs in connection with the Carriage of the Shipment as a result of such information and data and/or breach of such obligations (including, for exampleThe Principal undertakes to fully reimburse the Sender for such additional costs and at the same time to pay to the Sender the additional (usual) Remuneration assessed by the Sender in respect of such new circumstances of the Carriage, upon notice from the Sender to the Principal, with such additional costs and such additional Remuneration due within 5 working days of the date of delivery of such notice to the Sender. The Principal agrees that such additional costs and/or additional Remuneration may not be notified by the Sender prior to the performance of the Carriage (in particular in view of the nature and character of the Carriage).
7. Defects, liability for damages

7.1 The Principal shall ensure that the person receiving the Shipment at the Destination immediately inspects the contents and condition of the Shipment. If the contents of the Shipment have been degraded by the Shipment, this must be pointed out already upon receipt of the Shipment and the condition must be duly recorded (in particular by taking photographs).The Principal must deliver and forward the notification of the degradation of the Shipment, including the relevant documentation and photographs, to the Sender (usually by e-mail) at the latest within 5 working days from the date of receipt of the Shipment by the recipient. If the Sender fails to do so, the Sender loses its rights against the Sender in this respect.

7.2 In the event of defective performance of the GI by the Sender, the Principal shall be entitled to claim the relevant defects from the Sender (usually by e-mail) within 5 working days of their discovery at the latest. If the Principal fails to do so, the Principal loses its rights against the Freight Forwarder in this respect.

7.3 The Principal shall be liable for any damage incurred by the Sender or third parties as a result of a breach of the Principal's obligations under these GTC and/or the Forwarding Agreement, in particular, but not exclusively, as a result of a breach of the Principal's obligation to provide the Sender with correct and complete information about the contents of the Shipment and its nature, as well as about other facts necessary and/or required for the conclusion of the GTC and/or the contract of carriage and/or the procurement and/or performance of the Carriage of the Shipment.
7.4 The Sender shall be liable to the Principal for any damage caused by a breach of the Sender's obligations set out in these GTC and/or the GTC.

7.5 The Sender is only liable to the Principal for liabilities and damages arising in connection with the Carriage of the Shipment if the Sender carries out the Carriage of the Shipment himself/herself and/or if the Sender does not designate to the Principal the Carrier with whom the Sender arranges the Carriage of the Shipment. From the moment the Freight Forwarder identifies to the Principal the Carrier with whom the Freight Forwarder arranges for the Shipment to be transported, the Principal shall not be entitled to enforce against the Freight Forwarder any rights and claims for performance of the obligation under the related contract for the carriage of the Shipment and/or for compensation for damages, in full compliance with § 2482 CC in conjunction with § 2461 CC. In the event of any such claims by the Principal against the Carrier (upon designation of the Carrier by the Forwarder), the Forwarder shall assign the related rights (against the Carrier) to the Principal, if possible.

7.6 In cases where the Freight Forwarder is liable to the Principal for damages, the Freight Forwarder shall only be liable for actual damage to the Shipment during the procurement of the Carriage.Actual damage means the amount by which the value of the Shipment is reduced as a result of the damage event.
